<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10392454>
    dc:description "FIGURES 103–110. Neobisium (N.) vignai n. sp., female holotype, Grotta degli Ulivi (Amaseno, Latium) (unless otherwise stated). 103, epistome of carapace and right ocular area; 104, right chelicera, dorsal view; 105, male paratype, Grotta dell’Aretino (Prossedi, Latium): movable finger of right chelicera, dorsal view; 106, anterior processes of left coxa I; 107, trochanter, femur and patella of right pedipalp, dorsal view; 108, right pedipalpal chela, dorsal view; 109, same, antiaxial view, with magnified detail of teeth; 110, right leg IV, antiaxial view, with magnified detail of subterminal seta of telotarsus." ;
